            <abstract><p>Rejoices with Smith at "the happy event which has just taken place". Thanks Smith and his wife for the "kind &amp; continued attention" they have shown James, his son, [studying under Samuel Taylor, farmer, in Norfolk]. Looking forward to seeing Smith in Liverpool and eulogises their friendship. Sends regards to Mrs [Susannah] Taylor and [William Fitt] Drake.</p></abstract>
